HEADWORD: Clytie knot
<hw>Cly"tie knot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <def>In hair dressing, a loose, low
coil at the back of the head, like the knot on the head of the bust of
Clytie by <person>G. F. Watts</person>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

